<img src="http://68.media.tumblr.com/bbb9de9ecbfa0b42e56fd09b601e6302/tumblr_ohrg5q8h2z1qz4jbro1_500.jpg"/><br/><br/><p>My adventures in the world of cheap Chinese lights continue. At the moment I’m using a <a href="http://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/like/122249467777?lpid=122&chn=ps&adgroupid=33676502101&rlsatarget=pla-271883413835&adtype=pla&poi=&googleloc=9045669&device=c&campaignid=707291931&crdt=0" target="_blank"><b>Xeccon Striver 900</b></a> as my commuter light. The wide spread beam is OK, the spot beam less so - fine for road riding, not really up to mountain biking. However, it is staying on the bars despite bobbling round a bit when the going gets rough.</p><p>I’ve now supplemented it with one of these <a href="http://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/2000LM-CREE-XML-T6-LED-Bicycle-Bike-light-Head-Light-Lamp-With-Battery-UK-Stock-/331622924419?hash=item4d36444083:g:CcgAAOSwxN5WWA9B" target="_blank"><b>Cree 2000 lumen jobbies</b></a>, suggested by someone who’s used one for a year. It stays in place on the bars OK, with the battery package stashed in the Alpkit frame bag I leave permanently on the bike. Looks good so far, complementing the Xeccon light well to give a useable offroad combo. Early days yet, though…</p>